about.summary: Provides helper functions that make it easy to run 'BayesFactor' package tests on a data which is in a tidy format. Additionally, it provides a more consistent syntax and by default returns a dataframe with rich details. These functions can also return expressions containing results from Bayes Factor tests that can then be displayed on custom plots.

name: r-tidybf
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.2.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-tidybf
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/tidyBF_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/tidyBF/tidyBF_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3ec1aa0c81e90f89c4a0e6d20feedb8d3f8a4a3d0e40f62fb9ea1d8dff81855e

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-bayesfactor
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ipmisc
    - r-metabma
    - r-rlang
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-bayesfactor
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ipmisc
    - r-metabma
    - r-rlang
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('tidyBF')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('tidyBF')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://indrajeetpatil.github.io/tidyBF/, https://github.com/IndrajeetPatil/tidyBF
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Provides helper functions that make it easy to run 'BayesFactor' package tests on
    a data which is in a tidy format. Additionally, it provides a more consistent syntax
    and by default returns a dataframe with rich details. These functions can also return
    expressions containing results from Bayes Factor tests that can then be displayed
    on custom plots.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
